    • Method Detail

      • registerArgumentMapper

        <T> R registerArgumentMapper(java.lang.Class<T> type,
                             ArgumentTypePredicate predicate,
                             ArgumentTypeMapper<T> mapper)
        Registers an ArgumentMapper with the type provided.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type
        Parameters:
        type - the Type class
        predicate - This returns true if the CommandArgument can be mapped to the type. If the computation cost is similar to mapping the argument, leave this field null.
        mapper - the mapper

      • registerArgumentMapperSimple

        default <T> R registerArgumentMapperSimple(java.lang.Class<T> type,
                                           java.util.function.Predicate<CommandArgument> isType,
                                           java.util.function.Function<CommandArgument,T> getAsType)
        This ignores flags. Use registerArgumentMapper(java.lang.Class<T>, com.github.breadmoirai.breadbot.framework.internal.parameter.ArgumentTypePredicate, com.github.breadmoirai.breadbot.framework.internal.parameter.ArgumentTypeMapper<T>) otherwise.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type
        Parameters:
        type - The type class
        isType - predicate to test if the argument can be parsed to the type provided. This param can be left null if the complexity is close to getAsType.apply(arg) != null
        getAsType - A function to convert the argument to the type provided.
